Subject: [PATCH 06/23] dtb: imx6sxscm: add support for M4 and Linux dual boot

A new dts file imx6sxscm-1gb-evb-ldo-m4.dts is created for
supporting Linux and M4 dual booting.

To run a sample on the M4 you need to use the mmc dev 1
for the SD3 and use the proper dtb.

An example of how to change bootargs is as follows:

setenv fdt_file imx6sxscm-1gb-evb-ldo-m4.dtb

setenv mmcdev 1

setenv loadM4 'fatload mmc ${mmcdev} 0x80000000 \
               rpmsg_pingpong_freertos_example.bin; \
               dcache flush; cp.b 0x80000000 0x7F8000 0x8000; \
               dcache flush; bootaux 0x7F8000'

setenv mmcargs 'setenv bootargs console=${console},${baudrate} \
                uart_from_osc root=${mmcroot}'

setenv bootcmd 'run loadM4; mmc dev ${mmcdev};mmc dev ${mmcdev}; \
                if mmc rescan; then if run loadbootscript; \
                then run bootscript; else if run loadimage; \
                then run mmcboot; else run netboot; \
                fi; fi; else run netboot; fi'

